<span id="freeTextContainer12850534104557406555">I admire Leonard Peltier and I do believe that he is a political prisoner of the U.S. government. This book gives us Peltier&apos;s version of the 1973 siege at Wounded Knee, the events that followed, a brief account of his life in prison, dispersed with poetry and infused with Lakota spirituality. A great read.</span>
