<div id="review_4356072832" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4356072832" />
    <a title="Julio Pino" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25270689-julio-pino"><img alt="Julio Pino" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1383498460p2/25270689.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4356072832?book_show_action=true">Nov 25, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Julio Pino" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Julio Pino" href="/user/show/25270689-julio-pino">Julio Pino</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4356072832" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13831992508741644797">In the spirit of Crazy Horse, On this, Indigenous Resistance Day, I praise and hail the collected writings of Leonard Peltier, America&apos;s foremost political prisoner. This is not the story of his guilt or innocence (you can find that in the film INCIDENT AT OGLALA, narrated by Robert Redford) but of the clangs, clinks, shadows, and walls of the USA penal system, and the place reserved for those who dared cross the state. On the Rez or behind bars, the spirit of Peltier remains free.</span>
  <span id="freeText13831992508741644797" style="display:none">In the spirit of Crazy Horse, On this, Indigenous Resistance Day, I praise and hail the collected writings of Leonard Peltier, America's foremost political prisoner. This is not the story of his guilt or innocence (you can find that in the film INCIDENT AT OGLALA, narrated by Robert Redford) but of the clangs, clinks, shadows, and walls of the USA penal system, and the place reserved for those who dared cross the state. On the Rez or behind bars, the spirit of Peltier remains free.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13831992508741644797" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


